docs.abstract: Representative Thomas Massie of Kentucky objected to a request on Tuesday to pass a $19.1 billion emergency relief package by unanimous consent, becoming the second House Republican to block final passage.
docs.snippet: Representative Thomas Massie of Kentucky objected to a request on Tuesday to pass a $19.1 billion emergency relief package by unanimous consent, becoming the second House Republican to block final passage.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A single House Republican again blocked final passage of a long-delayed emergency aid package, the second Republican in a week to use the power of an individual lawmaker to ensure the delay of relief for communities and farmers still recovering from natural disasters.

headline.main: For Second Time, One Republican’s Objection Delays Disaster Aid
headline.print_headline: For Second Time in a Week, a Lone Republican’s Objection Delays Disaster Aid

docs.abstract: The move will return the border resolution to Congress, which is unlikely to garner the votes needed to override the veto.
docs.snippet: The move will return the border resolution to Congress, which is unlikely to garner the votes needed to override the veto.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Tuesday issued his second veto against legislation seeking to end his national emergency at the southwestern border, rejecting bipartisan objections to his efforts to obtain funds for a border wall.

headline.main: Trump Again Vetoes Measure to End National Emergency
headline.print_headline: Trump Vetoes Bill to End National Emergency at Border

docs.abstract: The vote fell short of the two-thirds majority needed to override President Trump’s veto, allowing him to continue circumventing Congress to fund the border wall.
docs.snippet: The vote fell short of the two-thirds majority needed to override President Trump’s veto, allowing him to continue circumventing Congress to fund the border wall.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate on Thursday failed to overturn President Trump’s veto of a resolution that would have terminated the national emergency he declared at the southwestern border. The defeat allows Mr. Trump to continue to defy Congress and divert federal funds to the construction of a border wall, his signature campaign promise.

headline.main: Senate Fails to Override Trump’s Veto, Keeping Border Emergency in Place
headline.print_headline: Failed Senate Vote Leaves  Border Emergency in Place

docs.abstract: After Speaker Nancy Pelosi accused him of a “cover-up,” the president said he would not work with Democrats until they stopped investigating him.
docs.snippet: After Speaker Nancy Pelosi accused him of a “cover-up,” the president said he would not work with Democrats until they stopped investigating him.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump abruptly blew up a meeting with Democratic congressional leaders on Wednesday, declaring that he could not work with them until they stopped investigating him and lashing out at Speaker Nancy Pelosi for accusing him of a cover-up.

headline.main: Trump, Angered by ‘Phony’ Inquiries, Blows Up Meeting With Pelosi and Schumer

docs.lead_paragraph: RHINEBECK, N.Y. — Even before Peter Plavchan Sr. asked about “the exact crimes” President Trump had committed to prompt his congressman to reverse course and embrace an impeachment inquiry, Representative Antonio Delgado was ready with a detailed answer.

headline.main: New York Democrats Balance Impeachment Issue With Local Concerns

docs.abstract: Democratic and Republican House leaders tried to broker a deal for an increase after a decade of frozen pay, but ran up against vulnerable freshman Democrats.
docs.snippet: Democratic and Republican House leaders tried to broker a deal for an increase after a decade of frozen pay, but ran up against vulnerable freshman Democrats.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Last week, a group of freshman Democrats — primarily from districts long held by Republicans — approached the House majority leader with a seemingly odd demand: Block our pay raises.

headline.main: A Truce Falters, and a Plan to Raise Congress’s Pay Falls Apart
headline.print_headline: Plan for a Congressional Pay Raise Falls Apart

docs.abstract: Facing opposition from both the Democratic Party’s liberal wing and fiscal hawks, House Democrats delayed voting on a budget measure that would increase spending.
docs.snippet: Facing opposition from both the Democratic Party’s liberal wing and fiscal hawks, House Democrats delayed voting on a budget measure that would increase spending.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Furious opposition from both the House Democrats’ most ardent liberals and their fiscal hawks forced Democratic leaders on Tuesday to delay voting on a two-year budget measure that would increase military and domestic spending, an embarrassing send-off as the new majority prepared to leave for a three-day retreat.

headline.main: Divided House Democrats Delay Budget Vote as Ideological Gap Widens
headline.print_headline: House Democrats Are Split on Spending, Delaying Vote on a Budget Measure

docs.abstract: Republicans defected by the dozens, despite President Trump’s endorsement and pressure from key outside groups, and Democrats were left to get the deal passed.
docs.snippet: Republicans defected by the dozens, despite President Trump’s endorsement and pressure from key outside groups, and Democrats were left to get the deal passed.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A divided House on Thursday passed a two-year budget deal that would raise spending by hundreds of billions of dollars over existing caps and allow the government to keep borrowing to cover its debts, amid grumbling from fiscal conservatives over the measure’s effect on the federal deficit.

headline.main: Divided House Passes 2-Year Budget Deal to Raise Spending
headline.print_headline: A Two-Year Budget Deal to Raise Spending Passes a Divided House

docs.abstract: The House again passed a massive bill to help the victims of floods, hurricanes and tornadoes, but President Trump’s opposition to Puerto Rico relief could doom it.
docs.snippet: The House again passed a massive bill to help the victims of floods, hurricanes and tornadoes, but President Trump’s opposition to Puerto Rico relief could doom it.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House on Friday again approved a huge emergency relief bill for farmers and communities hit by hurricanes, wildfires, floods and other natural disasters, escalating a standoff with President Trump, who has resisted more aid to Puerto Rico and demanded additional money for immigration enforcement.

headline.main: House Approves Disaster Relief and Puerto Rico Aid Over Trump’s Opposition
headline.print_headline: House Passes Disaster Aid Bill, Raising Pressure on Senate and President

docs.abstract: An emergency relief package, stymied for months, will finally go to President Trump. It allocates billions of dollars in relief for hurricanes, fires and floods.
docs.snippet: An emergency relief package, stymied for months, will finally go to President Trump. It allocates billions of dollars in relief for hurricanes, fires and floods.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Congress gave final approval on Monday to a long-delayed disaster aid package, ending the congressional impasse that has stymied efforts to send billions of dollars in relief to ongoing recovery efforts from a series of natural disasters.

headline.main: Congress Gives Final Approval to Long-Delayed Disaster Aid
headline.print_headline: Congress Signs Off on Disaster Aid Bill That Was Held Up for Months
